If you shall ask whether a soil be light or closer than is the wout—for one is friendly to corn, the other to the vine; the closer to Ceres, all the lightest to Lyaeus—you must first look out a place and bid a pit be sunk deep in the solid ground, then put all the earth back again, and tread the earth level at the top. If it fall short, this farm-land will be light, and better suited for the herd and gracious vine3 but if it shows that it cannot. return to its place, and if there is earth to spare when the pit is filled, the soil is stiff : look for reluctant clods and stiffness of ridge, and have strong oxen break your ground.
